Watts Advances Second Day in Chile on Report of $1 Billion Revenue Target

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-04-21T15:18:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/watts-advances-second-day-in-chile-on-report-of-1-billion-revenue-target.html
Watts SA (WATTS) , a Chilean food producer,
posted a record two-day increase after a report that the company
plans to reach $1 billion in annual revenue by 2015.  Watts gained 4.6 percent to 575 pesos at 11:01 a.m. New
York time. The shares have increased 9.5 percent in the past two
days.  Watts plans to increase revenue to $1 billion by 2015, the
company announced at its annual shareholder meeting,  Diario
Financiero  reported today, citing a company presentation. The
company posted annual revenue of 292 billion pesos ($625
million) in 2010, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Constanza Diaz, an officer at Watts’s communications
department, wasn’t available to comment, an assistant said by
phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
